In this episode of So This Happened, we reviewed the All Progressives Congress presidential primaries held during the past week and the emergence of Bola Tinubu as its candidate in the 2023 general election. We also reviewed the deadline of the Independent National Electoral Commission for the submission of running mates of candidates by political parties. Also reviewed was the arrest of an 18-year-old man who murdered a 36-year-old nursing mother and her one-year-old in Adamawa State. Lastly, we reviewed the attack in Ondo State by gunmen which left six persons dead just days after Owo massacre which happened at St. Francis Catholic Church, Owo. Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com